comments.author: MinerMEDIC
comments.body: A memory location can be altered by something as simple and random as a cosmic ray. I’m not even sure why they call them code editors. The only thing we use them for is copying. When you save your EEPROM image make sure to note the board, board version, board subversion e.g. A8V3 and temp sensor. You may get away with using a different subversion But you will never get it be with using the wrong temp sensor.
